and compile my review.\n\n**PR Summary:**\n- PR #10, branch feat/issue-7\n- 14 f
iles changed, +992/-1169 lines\n- Migrates city-builder UI components to a new b
ase UI layer (src/ui/)\n- Components: BuildingDetailPanel, BuildingSelector, Con
firmationDialog, RemoveConfirmDialog, TopInfoBar, UpgradeConfirmDialog\n\n**Code
Style Review:**\n1. **Naming conventions**: All classes use PascalCase, interfac
es use PascalCase, variables use camelCase. Good.\n2. **Unused imports**: In `Bu
ildingDetailPanel.ts`, `ServerBuildingStatus` is imported but used. Good.\n3. **
In `BuildingSelector.ts`**: The `ResourceDisplay` interface in `TopInfoBar.ts` c
hanged from `icon` to `label`. Good.\n4. **TypeScript issues**:\n   - In `Confir
mationDialog.ts`, the class extends `UIDialog` but has a `destroy()` method that
just calls `super.destroy()`. This is redundant but harmless.\n   - `Confirmatio
nDialog.show()` calls `dialog.show()` but the `show` method in `ConfirmationDial
og` doesn\'t pass config to `super.show()`. Actually looking at it:\n     ```typ
escript\n     show(config?: Partial<ConfirmationDialogConfig>): void {\n       i
f (config) {\n         if (config.title !== undefined) {\n           // UIDialog
不支持动态更新标题/消息，需要重建\n           // 这里简化处理：如果需要完全动态
更新，建议直接使用 UIDialog\n         }\n         if (config.onConfirm) this.con
firmCallback = config.onConfirm;\n         if (config.onCancel) this.cancelCallb
ack = config.onCancel;\n       }\n       super.show();\n     }\n     ```\n     T
his is a bit problematic - if config.title/message changes, it won\'t be reflect
ed. But this is noted in the comment and marked as `@deprecated`.\n\n5. **Archit
ecture Compliance (for TS project)**:\n   - The components correctly import from
`../../ui/...` instead of duplicating UI primitives.\n   - No circular dependenc
ies visible.\n   - `BuildingSelector` now uses `UIList` instead of custom grid. 
This changes the UX from a 2x3 grid to a vertical list. The PR description menti
ons this explicitly.\n\n6. **Potential issues I noticed:**\n   - In `BuildingDet
ailPanel.ts`, the `costContainer` is created but uses `removeAll(true)` in `upda
teUpgradeCost`. Since it\'s added to `panel` content, when panel is destroyed, i
t should be fine. But `removeAll(true)` destroys children which is correct.\n   
- In `RemoveConfirmDialog.ts`, `destroy()` method calls `this.panel?.destroy()` 
then `super.destroy()`. However, since `panel` is already a child of `this` Cont
ainer, calling `super.destroy()` should also destroy panel. But explicit destroy
is fine.\n   - `TopInfoBar.ts`: The `ResourceDisplay` interface changed `icon` t
o `label`. This is an intentional change since it now uses `UIIcon` which doesn\
't take a string emoji label. Wait, looking more carefully:\n     ```typescript\
n     private readonly resourceConfigs: ResourceDisplay[] = [\n       { key: \'g
old\', label: \'灵石\', color: \'#ffd700\' },\n       ...\n     ];\n     ```\n  
  But in `createResourceInfo`:\n     ```typescript\n     const icon = new UIIcon
(this.scene, {\n       x: x - 40,\n       y,\n       size: 20,\n       fallbackC
olor: 0x333333,\n       strokeColor: 0x666666,\n     });\n     ```\n     The `UI
Icon` is created without a texture, so it will just show a colored rectangle. Th
e old code used emoji icons like `💰`. This is a **regression** in UX - the reso
urce icons in the top bar lost their emoji labels and now show empty colored rec
tangles.\n\n     Actually, wait - looking at `UIIcon`, it only supports `texture
` (image) or a fallback rectangle. There\'s no text/emoji fallback. So yes, the 
resource icons are now just blank rectangles.\n\n     This is a **blocking issue
** - the UI lost its visual icons for resources.\n\n7. **In `BuildingSelector.ts
`**:\n   - The old code had emoji icons for each building type. The new code use
s `UIList` which supports `icon` property on `UIListItem`. But the new code does
n\'t set icons:\n     ```typescript\n     const items: UIListItem[] = this.build
ingIds.map((id) => {\n       const def = BuildingDefinitions[id];\n       return
{\n         id,\n         label: def ? `${def.name} (${def.width}x${def.height})
` : id,\n         data: def,\n       };\n     }).filter(item => item.data);\n   
 ```\n     It could have added `icon: this.getBuildingIcon(id)` but removed the 
`getBuildingIcon` method entirely. This is another loss of visual richness, thou
gh not as severe as the top bar since the list now shows names explicitly.\n\n8.
**Test issues**:\n   - `ConfirmationDialog.test.ts` has tests named "should call
onConfirm callback" and "should call onCancel callback" but they never actually 
call the callbacks. They just create the dialog and call `show()`. This is a mis
leading test name. However, this is pre-existing behavior or the tests are weak.
